OL,3,CCumbria set for elected mayor after
OL,4,Ccouncil approval
OL,6,FCumbria is now in position to receive
OL,7,F#333 million over the next 30 years
OL,8,Fwith access to the Cumbrian Mayoral
OL,9,FInvestment Fund, with both Cumberland
OL,10,FCouncil and Westmorland and Furness
OL,11,FCouncil having an equal voice on
OL,12,Fcouncil matters with the mayor.
OL,14,FThe mayor will take over the powers of
OL,15,Fthe Cumbria Police, Fire and Crime
OL,16,FCommissioner and will have a seat
OL,17,Falongside other mayors at the Council
OL,18,Fof Nations and Regions and the Great
OL,19,FNorth Mayors' Group. These groups
OL,20,Ffocus on energy, transport, rural
OL,21,Fgrowth and defence.
